{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QYP4tMhGKSmA6piMUtDK4H","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The stop hook is asking me to do a self-review of the changes I just made. Let me review the changes I made to `title-extractor.ts`.\n\nThe changes were:\n1. Added `|| isSectionLabel(trimmed)` to `allPrecedingFiltered` check\n2. Added structural preamble detection with +0.12 bonus vs +0.08\n3. Added cap for combined positional boost at 0.15\n\nLet me review these quickly myself rather than spinning up a full code-review-expert agent, since the changes are small and focused.\n\nKey things to check:\n1. No TODOs or placeholders - clean\n\n\n2. Code purpose is clear\n3. No duplicate logic to consolidate\n4. Consistency with rest of codebase\n\nThe changes look clean. The `baseScoreBeforePositionalBonuses` captures `baseScore` which excludes position factor (since `baseScore = rawScore + allCapsBonus + structuralBonus` from line 994). So `firstCandidate.score - baseScoreBeforePositionalBonuses` correctly isolates the position factor contribution plus preamble bonus, which is what I need to cap at 0.15.\n\nThe calculation is sound—`totalPositionalBoost` properly accounts for both the multiplicative position factor and additive preamble bonus that were applied during the `.map()` operation. The code is clean and serves its purpose well, so I'll move forward with this approach.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":295,"cache_read_input_tokens":27684,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":295},"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"7bb8f7ed-0545-40aa-a990-96627925b60c","uuid":"14089f91-5e69-4f84-b033-a3e1dfe6c5b7"}
